page.title: 02ECOLOGY IN CHINGFORD
page.content: We visited the woodland area and lakes around Highams Park.The woodland area ,a part of Epping Forest,is generally quiet with a few people fishing in the boating lake.There are many varieties of trees including Beech,Wild Cherry, Willow,Oak,Conifer and some Holly and Hawthorn bushes.On the lake there coots,moorhens,ducks and swans.The birds that the class saw in the area were blackbirds,thrushes,sparrows, robins,pigeons and black headed gulls. Wild flowers were everywhere these included,Fever Few,Skull Cap,Wood Caliment,Lesser Cats Tail,Buttercup, Cow Parsley.Poppies,Golden Rod,Silver Fir and Meadow Barley.Most of the veg- etation is uncultivated. Epping Forest originally belonged to the crown,it was a from Queen Victoria to the people of London.The river Ching flows to Highams Park Lake.
